USER RESEARCH
================================================================================
TOP 5 PAIN POINTS (from forums, Quora, industry data):
  1. Chipping within 2–3 days — the #1 complaint. Summer conditions (sunscreen,
     swimming, heat, constant hand-washing) accelerate this. 45% of at-home
     mani users cite this as their biggest frustration.
  2. Hidden UV lamp requirement — buyers purchase a gel set and discover they
     need £30–£80 of extra equipment. Biggest source of 1-star Amazon reviews
     for gel kits. Complete starter kits that include a lamp solve this directly.
  3. Colour looks nothing like the bottle/photo — consistent complaint in Amazon
     reviews and brand FAQs. Digital-to-physical colour mismatch frustrates
     repeat buyers.
  4. Too many unusable colours in large sets — buyers use 3–4 shades from a
     20-colour set. Curated 6–8 colour sets aligned to actual summer palettes
     outperform in usage satisfaction.
  5. Overwhelming choice — decision paralysis. Market is flooded with copycat
     brands. Buyers want one clear trusted recommendation, not 30 options.

